1) Fix the `LEVEL' value in the Makefile
2)
make
3) create a test file. Dummy example:
#include <stdlib.h>
int main()
{
        long long int denom = 0;
        lldiv(10, denom);
        return 0;
}
4) assuming the name of the file created in (3) is test.c:
clang -emit-llvm -o test.bc test.c
5)
clang -emit-llvm -o warning.bc warning.c
6)
llvm-link warning.bc test.bc -S -o=all.bc
7) Assuming mac OS:
../../../../Debug+Asserts/bin/opt -load ../../../../Debug+Asserts/lib/BlackListed.dylib -integersBlacklisting < all.bc > target.bc
(needs changes since this is the command for the default `LEVEL' value)
8) Run
lli target.bc
9) To view the IR:
llvm-dis target.bc
cat target.ll
